=== T10 RE-RUN after Rule 1 prose-invert fix @ 2026-05-11T22:42Z
=========================================================================

Discovered during T11 screenshot review: every prose `<h1>` and `<p>` on
/help rendered WHITE on warm-paper (invisible body text). Root cause:
`<article className="prose prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-none">`
in HelpLayout (Plan 07-02 source). The dashboard's theme system
(packages/spa/src/lib/theme.ts) defaults to `dark` mode (D-02) and adds
the `dark` class to <html>, so `dark:prose-invert` fired everywhere.
Phase 7 CONTEXT.md mis-assumed v1.0 ships "no .dark{} block; dark:
prose-invert is dormant" — but the class is present app-wide.

Rule 1 fix: remove `dark:prose-invert` from HelpLayout article (light
prose only in v1.0; dark-mode prose deferred to v1.1 per D-7-12).
Updated HelpLayout.test.tsx accordingly. All 715 vitest tests + 16/16
Playwright still green.

Re-measurement after fix:

| Antipattern  | Pre-fix | Post-fix | Distinct pairs                       |
|--------------|---------|----------|--------------------------------------|
| low-contrast | 27      | 5        | (post) #9c95a8 on #fafaf7 (only)    |

The 5 remaining findings are all `text-text-tertiary` (#9c95a8) at 2.8:1
against the warm-paper bg — the inherited Phase 5.1 token used for
"(soon)" stub tags. Pre-existing, not Plan 07-05's fault. The white-
on-paper false-positives (22 findings) are GONE — those were the
prose h1/p elements that ACTUALLY rendered white before the fix.

Verdict: T10 is now operationally green for Plan 07-05. Even without a
composite score, all "Plan 07-05's own component additions" findings
are zero. The 5 inherited token findings are noted for v1.0.1.
